TASK_DESCRIPTION=CATEGORY: deep
MODEL: opus

Execute ALL 8 decisions from the Doey storage architecture audit. This is a large cross-cutting refactor touching shell scripts, hooks, Go TUI, and runtime directories.

PHASED EXECUTION ORDER (by dependency):

PHASE 1 — Quick cleanups (independent, parallel-safe):
- Decision 4: Remove dead lifecycle/ directory (common.sh writer + ensure_runtime_dirs entry + purge logic)
- Decision 6: Clean up DOEY_PROJECT ghost references (audit skills/agents, replace with DOEY_PROJECT_DIR or PROJECT_DIR)
- Decision 3: Add stats allowlist sync check to doey doctor

PHASE 2 — Heartbeat merge:
- Decision 2: Merge dual heartbeat into single status/<pane>.heartbeat. Update post-tool-lint.sh, doey-ctl observe, remove heartbeat/ dir.

PHASE 3 — IPC cleanup:
- Decision 5: Wire pending/ delivery into taskmaster-wait.sh OR remove pending/ queue entirely (prefer removal if not needed — simpler).

PHASE 4 — SQLite as single source of truth (biggest change):
- Decision 1: Rewire task pipeline. doey-ctl writes SQLite only + auto-exports .task. Shell helpers become read-only wrappers. SyncTaskFiles becomes one-way export. Eliminate tasks.json. Runtime cache from SQLite.

PHASE 5 — New features:
- Decision 7: doey config show command (full merge chain resolution)
- Decision 8: Evaluate status/ fan-out — research + design only (consolidate to per-pane JSON). May produce a follow-up task.

KEY FILES (from audit): See origin prompt for complete file references across shell/, hooks, and tui/.

IMPORTANT: Each phase should be validated (go build, test-bash-compat.sh, doey doctor) before moving to the next. Decision 1 (Phase 4) is the riskiest — research current task flow thoroughly before touching it.
